{"message": "I definitely lean toward deep, focused conversations. There's something satisfying about really sinking into a topic — peeling back layers, following threads, getting somewhere meaningful rather than just skimming the surface. When we jump around too much, I feel like we're collecting dots without ever connecting them.

That said, I'm not rigid about it. Some of the best conversations start in one place and wander somewhere unexpected. But the wandering feels worthwhile when there's still a sense of depth along the way, not just a rapid-fire exchange of shallow takes. I'd rather leave a conversation having really understood something — or someone — better than before.

What about you?"}
